        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001151": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001151",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001152": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001152",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Excluding the chapters he identified as Middle (which ended up being assigned very evenly across the other three layers), none of these completely disagree with Emerson’s assignments (except for 52, which is the only entire chapter he considered to be Added), although he assigns some sections of some chapters to other layers.  While a significant majority (85%) of the chapters were <span class=\"c5\">strongly</span> identified as belonging to their layer (the underlined chapters above), the pattern recognition process did indicate that a few (most notably chapters 24, 45, 46, 59, and 62, and to a lesser extent 8, 22, 30, 39, 44, and 49) may have elements of more than one layer present within them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001153": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001153",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001154": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001154",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001155": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001155",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001156": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001156",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Note that while Emerson’s names (Early, Late, Post-Guodian) are kept for convenience, they don’t necessarily have to indicate separation in time – they could perhaps represent different oral traditions, or sayings that originally developed in different regions of China, which combined to form the Dao De Jing we know today.  Also note that the Guodian document (~300 BCE) consists of chapters from both Early and Late in roughly equal numbers, so this “layering” actually happened very early.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001157": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001157",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001158": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001158",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001159": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001159",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001160": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001160",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Although chapter 40 was identified as being strongly Post-Guodian, it is present in the Guodian manuscript, but that is not considered a major problem. For example, if perhaps the post-Guodian “style” was already being developed at the time the Guodian document was created, then the presence of chapter 40 in the document could mean that it had already been written in this style, perhaps shortly before the Guodian document was created, whereas chapters 68-81 had yet to be written (or the Guodian compiler was not aware of their existence).  There are probably many other scenarios that could explain such a result.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001161": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001161",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001162": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001162",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001163": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001163",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001164": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001164",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-8b1105 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-65f006 twpub-1a2844f534b920c9-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"WordSection1\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Chapter 2 was variously classified as belonging to all three layers, but the symbol distributions (below) simultaneously indicated that it cannot belong to any of them!  If any chapter is truly a mixture of layers, it is this one (which Emerson agrees with), so it is not assigned to any.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001165": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1a2844f534b920c9/text/000001165",
